default6default. defaultLegislationdefault&#xa0;default6.1
default              
defaultThe 
defaultHighway Codedefault needs to be updated, so 
defaultit is less focused on motorised vehicles, and more inclusive of the safety-enhancing needs of other road users including cyclists. This could include stating a 
defaultminimum space between vehicles and bikesdefault, both while passing and before and after overtaking. 
default6
default.2
default              
defaultConsideration of introducing a 
default“presumption of guilt” defaultlaw, such as operates in other continental European countries, whereby in
default the event of a collision between a cyclists and a motorised vehicle, the driver of the latter is automatically assumed to be 
defaultat fault, unless it can be proved otherwise. This legislative approach appears to cement an attitude of greater respect for cyclists’ safety and well-being from drivers.
